This paper is primarily focused on object recognition using deep convolutional neural networks, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of generative models and feedback connections in the visual system, which could potentially fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also proposes a new training method for neural networks, which could fall under the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the discovery of new patterns in data, which could potentially fall under the statistical learning (cs.SD) sub-category.
